member.name: WinRT.HSTRING_UserFree
member.summary: Frees resources on the server side when called by RPC stub files.

member.summary: Frees resources on the server side when called by RPC stub files.

member.name: WinRT.HSTRING_UserMarshal
member.summary: Marshals an HSTRING object into the RPC buffer.
member.param: The current buffer. This pointer may or may not be aligned on entry.
member.returns: The value obtained from the returned HRESULT value is S_OK.

member.name: WinRT.HSTRING_UserMarshal64
member.summary: Marshals an HSTRING object into the RPC buffer.
member.param: The current buffer. This pointer may or may not be aligned on entry.
member.returns: The value obtained from the returned HRESULT value is S_OK.

member.name: WinRT.HSTRING_UserSize
member.summary: Calculates the wire size of the HSTRING object, and gets its handle and data.
member.param: The current buffer offset where the object will be marshaled. The method has to account for any padding needed for the HSTRING object to be properly aligned when it will be marshaled to the buffer.
member.returns: The value obtained from the returned HRESULT value is S_OK.

member.summary: Calculates the wire size of the HSTRING object, and gets its handle and data.
member.param: The current buffer offset where the object will be marshaled. The method has to account for any padding needed for the HSTRING object to be properly aligned when it will be marshaled to the buffer.
member.returns: The value obtained from the returned HRESULT value is S_OK.

member.name: WinRT.HSTRING_UserUnmarshal
member.summary: Unmarshals an HSTRING object from the RPC buffer.
member.param: The current buffer. This pointer may or may not be aligned on entry.

returns.para: The value obtained from the returned HRESULT value is one of the following.

listheader.description: Insufficient memory for this function to perform.
